cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SD 

The paper discusses auto-encoders and their extensions, specifically gated auto-encoders, which are commonly used in deep learning for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of the models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses deep learning benchmarks, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
